 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-ibuuh","title":"EPIC: Default hybrid search with self-healing lexical index and low-impact semantic backfill","description":"BACKGROUND:
The current canonical SQLite artifact is healthy and the Tantivy lexical index is complete, but normal cass search still defaults to lexical mode and hybrid/two-tier search hard-fails when semantic/vector assets are missing. That is the wrong product contract for AI-agent-first search. The desired contract is: hybrid intent should be the default experience, lexical search must always remain immediately available, and semantic refinement should opportunistically improve results without ever making ordinary search unusable.

PRODUCT INTENT:
1. SQLite canonical DB is the sole source of truth.
2. Tantivy lexical index is a mandatory derivative artifact and must be rebuilt automatically from SQLite whenever missing, corrupt, schema-drifted, fingerprint-mismatched, or otherwise unusable.
3. Semantic/vector assets are optional derivative artifacts. Their absence must never break ordinary search; the system must fail open to lexical results.
4. Hybrid search should be the default behavior presented by the CLI/TUI/robot interface, but the default must preserve lexical immediacy and reliability.
5. Semantic backfill should happen in the background when the machine is idle or when work can be done within a strict performance budget, with pause/resume/checkpoint behavior.
6. Status/health/capabilities must report lexical readiness and semantic readiness separately, truthfully, and in a way that lets agents reason about whether they are seeing lexical-only or hybrid-refined results.

WHY THIS MATTERS:
The over-arching goal of cass is that a coding agent can point it at a canonical session history database and trust it to be searchable immediately, without needing to understand the implementation details of lexical vs semantic indexing. Search should not require a manual repair workflow. The system should self-heal mandatory search artifacts and opportunistically enrich itself in the background.

SCOPE OF THIS EPIC:
- Redefine search/index asset ownership and state semantics
- Make lexical index regeneration automatic and safe
- Make hybrid the default search intent while failing open to lexical
- Add background semantic backlog tracking, scheduling, and resumable execution
- Add truthful observability for lexical vs semantic readiness
- Add exhaustive tests and operator docs
- Prove the design on the live canonical artifact after implementation

NON-GOALS:
- Do not make semantic availability a prerequisite for ordinary search
- Do not require users/agents to memorize manual repair commands for lexical correctness
- Do not perform heavy background work aggressively enough to harm foreground coding or search latency

SUCCESS CRITERIA FOR THE EPIC:
- A missing or invalid Tantivy index self-heals from the SQLite DB without user intervention.
- Ordinary cass search commands default to hybrid intent but still succeed quickly when semantic assets are absent.
- Background semantic backfill can resume across interruptions and converges to a fully indexed corpus.
- Health/status surfaces clearly distinguish lexical-ready, semantic-ready, and semantic-backfilling states.
- The implementation is covered by integration tests that simulate the real failure modes this epic is meant to eliminate.

PLANNING NOTE:
This epic is the source of truth for the new architecture. Any older beads that treated progressive/hybrid search as optional prior art should be treated as historical context only, not as the final plan.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-31T18:16:06.291767609Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-31T18:25:37.141431403Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["hybrid","indexing","search","self-healing","semantic","tantivy"],"comments":[{"id":505,"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-ibuuh","author":"ubuntu","text":"Audit pass on 2026-03-31 using bv --robot-plan / --robot-insights / --robot-priority / --robot-suggest. Main conclusions: (1) bead .1 is correctly the keystone; (2) the original graph had one real sequencing bug, with user-facing default-hybrid flip ordered ahead of the fail-open hybrid runtime; (3) the plan was under-specified on semantic model/tier policy and on reusable fault-injection/e2e logging harnesses; (4) we should preserve strong per-bead testing requirements and treat the final test bead as additive cross-system validation, not a dumping ground for all tests. Revisions below are intended to reduce ambiguity and improve implementation safety without dropping any functionality.","created_at":"2026-03-31T18:25:37Z"}]}
 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-ibuuh.1","title":"Define search asset contract, fingerprints, and state machine","description":"BACKGROUND:
Today cass mixes several different concepts: SQLite source-of-truth health, Tantivy lexical completeness, freshness timestamps, semantic/vector availability, and background work progress. Different call sites infer readiness in different ways, which produces brittle behavior and wrong user-facing conclusions. This bead creates the single authoritative state model that every other bead in the epic will rely on.

GOAL:
Define and implement the canonical search asset contract for cass. The result should make it unambiguous which artifacts are required, which are optional, how each artifact is fingerprinted against SQLite, and how runtime code decides whether to rebuild, reuse, backfill, wait, or fail open.

SCOPE:
- Declare SQLite canonical DB as the only source of truth.
- Declare Tantivy lexical index as a mandatory derivative artifact.
- Declare fast-tier vector index, quality-tier vector index, and any ANN/HNSW accelerators as optional derivative artifacts.
- Define authoritative fingerprints/manifests that tie derivative assets to the SQLite corpus version and schema version.
- Define explicit runtime states such as: missing, building, ready, stale, fingerprint-mismatch, corrupt, partially-available, and backfilling.
- Define what is blocking vs non-blocking for each asset class.
- Define lock ownership rules so only one repair/build publisher wins while readers remain safe.
- Replace ad hoc heuristics in status/health/search gating with calls into a shared state loader/evaluator.

DESIGN CONSIDERATIONS:
- State must distinguish completeness from recency. A corpus can be complete-but-old and still searchable.
- State must distinguish lexical-required failures from semantic-optional degradation.
- Fingerprints must be cheap enough to check often and stable enough to avoid false rebuilds.
- The contract must support interrupted builds and atomic publish/swap.
- Future self should be able to answer "why did cass rebuild this asset" by inspecting the state payload, not by reverse-engineering logs.

TEST/VALIDATION REQUIREMENTS:
- Unit tests for state classification from manifest inputs.
- Tests for fingerprint mismatch vs pure staleness vs corruption.
- Tests proving the same evaluator is used by search, status, and health paths.

DONE WHEN:
There is one authoritative state model that can answer, for any data dir, whether lexical search is ready, whether semantic refinement is ready, whether background backfill is needed, and what remediation path is required.","notes":"TEST POLICY ADDENDUM: This bead must land with bead-local validation, not just final-epic validation. At minimum include targeted unit tests for the new invariants, integration tests for the affected runtime path, and at least one CLI/robot/E2E script when the behavior is user-visible or multi-step. Test output must include rich, structured, timestamped logging and artifact snapshots sufficient for a future agent to diagnose failures without rerunning the entire scenario manually. Prefer extending the shared harness from coding_agent_session_search-ibuuh.15 where applicable.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-03-31T18:16:45.529211893Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-31T20:17:44.052486548Z","closed_at":"2026-03-31T20:17:44.051794241Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["indexing","search","semantic","state-model","tantivy"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-ibuuh.1","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-ibuuh","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-31T18:16:45.529211893Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
